  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Chopped-cherry-tomatoes-1591104049058-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Chopped-cherry-tomatoes-1591104049058-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Chopped-cherry-tomatoes-1591104049058-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Chopped-cherry-tomatoes-1591104049058-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Chopped-cherry-tomatoes-1591104049058-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the woody ends off the <strong>asparagus</strong></p><p>Tip: Alternatively, bend the woody ends of the asparagus until they snap!</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken breasts</strong>, <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>asparagus</strong> to a baking tray</p><p>Drizzle with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580124957216-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580124957216-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580124957216-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580124957216-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1580124957216-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the vegetables are tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580124961436-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580124961436-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580124961436-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580124961436-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1580124961436-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is in the oven, add the <strong>wheat berries</strong> to a pot with plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook over a high heat for 12-15 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, add the <strong>baby leaf spinach</strong> to the pot, stir it all together, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580124965466-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580124965466-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580124965466-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580124965466-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580124965466-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1580124968944-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1580124968944-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1580124968944-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1580124968944-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1580124968944-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) and <strong>chopped basil</strong> to a <strong>pestle and mortar</strong> with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and grind to a paste</p><p>Add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and the <strong>juice</strong> of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lemon</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>basil oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1580124972058-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1580124972058-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1580124972058-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1580124972058-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1580124972058-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything is cooked, add the <strong>juices</strong> from the roasting tray to the wheat berries and stir it all together</p><p>Finely slice the <strong>cooked chicken</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1580124976441-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1580124976441-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1580124976441-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1580124976441-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1580124976441-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sliced chicken</strong> with the<strong> roasted asparagus</strong> and <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong>, <strong>wheat berries</strong> and <strong>lemon wedge</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>basil oil</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
